Introduction

VNT (브이엔티) was a Korean pop girl group created by Media Line. Their group name is an acronym that stands for "Voice of Ninety Two" due to all three of the members being born in the year 1992. Only four months after their debut, in March 21, 2011, Lil J announced through her personal Twitter that she had left the group, and VNT disbanded soon after.
